                <h2>2. Southwest Airlines Pet Fee</h2>
                <p>Now, you need to understand the pet fee or pet fare in Southwest according to the airline's pet policy. Right now, the pet traveling fee is $95 each way per pet carrier. This fee is non-refundable and must be paid at the airport ticket counter. The airline does not allow pets to fly free, even for Rapid Rewards members.</p>
                <h2>3. Pet Carrier Guidelines</h2>
                <p>On the other hand, if you want to fly with Southwest, you must use an airline-approved pet carrier that meets the following requirements. Here are the rules to know -</p>
                <p><b>Size Limit:</b> The carrier must fit under the seat and not exceed 18.5" x 8.5" x 13.5" (L x H x W).</p>
                <p><b>Types of Carriers:</b> Both soft-sided and hard-sided carriers are allowed.</p>
                <p><b>Ventilation:</b> The carrier must have proper ventilation to keep the pet comfortable.</p>
                <p><b>Secure Closure:</b> The carrier must zip or close securely so the pet remains inside during the flight.</p>
                <p>Southwest sells branded pet carriers at the airport for $58, but you can also bring your own as long as it meets the airline's standards.</p>
