                <p>The airline no longer allows emotional support animals on flights. However, trained service animals are permitted under specific guidelines. As per the policy, only dogs are accepted as service animals, and the animals must be fully qualified to assist a person with a disability. Passengers traveling with service animals must complete a U.S. Department of Transportation. No extra fee is required for service animals.</p>
                <h2>5. Important Rules and Restrictions</h2>
